I have been working on a <https://github.com/jackmpcollins/magentic|Python package >`magentic` that makes using openai function calling as easy as writing python function signatures. My goal today is to have one project use this (it could be yours!). As Harrison said earlier OpenAI function calling and custom prompts are the best tools to use for your hackathon project, and `magentic` is built to enable exactly that! <https://github.com/jackmpcollins/magentic>

<!channel> Instructions for using the *MultiOn API*:
• Please come to the desks near the presentation area for signing our Hackathon Participation form & getting any support
• You can directly use MultiOn from *Langchain*: <https://python.langchain.com/docs/modules/agents/toolkits/multion>
• You can also check our API examples and also build custom agents directly using our *python & js sdk*s : <https://github.com/MULTI-ON/api>
• Here's an example agent built with MultiOn API to scrape information online & send back a screenshot: <https://github.com/MULTI-ON/api/blob/main/examples/Multion_api_example.ipynb>
• You can find *documentation* & installation instructions for MultiOn here: <https://docs.multion.ai/>
• Finally we are building a *Skills Marketplace* for MultiOn and please reach out to us if you want to help build it :star-struck:

Been working on creating a strong multi-action-agent.

A week ago I watched a friend copying prompts and using GPT to answer questions for an accelerator, said he planned to apply to every accelerator and incubator and pre-seed firm, had a link list of 1,200 different.

I thought that had to have been automated already, but came up with nothing. Thus working on a complete AutoFormFiller today, working on optimizing it, sample demo below. DM me to join up / help.

We first evaluate if the data file uploaded will provide a good answer, and when it doesn't have the data, it prompts user entry, and saves the response for future responses

Also quick idea for anyone searching, that I plan to explore in the future, I've used applications like UbotStudio and Zennoposter which are no-code browser automation tools, they include multi-threading, headless browsing, captcha breaking. Would love to see an LLM agent built on top of those platforms. Seems it would take the multi-action-agent space much further by building on top of these systems.

I’m very open to hacking and collaborating with others re the above ideas! If you have a compelling concept related to the above, or if the above is interesting to you (and you’re a big Typescript fan), please DM me! or respond to this thread :)
As part of strong type systems in Typescript in particular, I also have the `<https://github.com/poteat/hkt-toolbelt> project, which is a composable framework for higher-kinded types in Typescript.

As well, roughly I’m also interested in integrating strong type systems with LLMs - strong type systems (in the realm of proof-based languages, i.e. Lean from Microsoft, Coq, Idris, Ada, etc.) have the capability to ensure that the code that LLMs are generated is correct (via formal postconditions)

Hey everyone, Lei Zhao here. Couldn’t wait to meet y’all tmrw. I’m passion about 2ndBrain, and some idea related to this: 
1. *KnwoledgeAgent*: extract *knowledge graph* out of a content (could be article, podcast, or even video) using *LLM*. Find similar or contradictory opinion across different contents. 
2. *FactAgent*: scrape the fact based on predetermined source to add to 2ndBrain based on concept or keyword. 
I might also open to other ideas if related to knowledge.  Looking forward for tmrw’s challenge.
